---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro'
import FHEDemo from '../../components/security/FHEDemo'
---

<MainLayout title="FHE Demo | Gradiant">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1
      class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
    >
      Fully Homomorphic Encryption Demo
    </h1>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-8">
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
        This demo showcases Gradiant's implementation of Fully Homomorphic
        Encryption (FHE), which allows computation on encrypted data without
        decryption. This technology is crucial for maintaining privacy in
        sensitive therapy conversations.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
        FHE enables our AI models to analyze therapy content, detect risk
        patterns, and generate insights while keeping the original content
        encrypted and secure.
      </p>

      <div
        class="bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-900 p-4 rounded-md text-yellow-800 dark:text-yellow-200 mb-8"
      >
        <strong>Note:</strong> This is a simplified demonstration of the FHE capabilities.
        The actual implementation includes more advanced features such as:
        <ul class="list-disc pl-8 mt-2">
          <li>Homomorphic sentiment analysis</li>
          <li>Encrypted content categorization</li>
          <li>Risk pattern detection in encrypted text</li>
          <li>Secure key management with automatic rotation</li>
          <li>Multi-level security modes (Standard, HIPAA, FHE)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <FHEDemo client:load />

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white">
        How Fully Homomorphic Encryption Works
      </h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">
            1. Encryption
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Client data is encrypted before transmission using FHE algorithms,
            creating a mathematical representation that preserves the structure
            of the data while making it unreadable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">
            2. Computation
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Specialized algorithms work directly on the encrypted data,
            performing calculations and analysis without ever decrypting the
            information.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">
            3. Results
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            The encrypted results are returned to the client, where they can be
            decrypted using private keys that never left the client's device.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200"
      >
        <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3">Security and Compliance</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Our FHE implementation exceeds HIPAA requirements for protecting
          patient data and provides an additional layer of security beyond
          standard encryption methods.
        </p>
        <p>
          By processing data while it remains encrypted, we eliminate the
          vulnerability window that exists when data must be decrypted for
          analysis in traditional systems.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
